{"title_page": "The Stanfields", "text_new": "{{About|the Canadian [[folk rock]] band|the textile company|Stanfield%27s}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name = The Stanfields\n| background = group_or_band\n| image = The_Stanfields_-_Group_Photo.png\n| caption = From left to right: Dillan Tate, Jason MacIsaac, Jon Landry, Calen Kinney, and Mark Murphy\n| image_size =\n| genre = [[Folk rock]], [[punk rock]]\n| years_active        = {{Start date|2008}}\u2013present\n| origin = [[Halifax Regional Municipality|Halifax]], [[Nova Scotia]], Canada\n| label = Groundswell Music/[[Warner Music Canada]]. Rookie Records(EU)\n| associated_acts     =\n| website = http://www.thestanfields.ca\n| current_members = Jon Landry<br>Dillan Tate<br>Jason MacIsaac<br>Calen Kinney<br>Mark Murphy\n}}\n\n'''The Stanfields''' are a [[Canada|Canadian]] rock music group, based in [[Halifax Regional Municipality|Halifax]], [[Nova Scotia]].<ref name=metro>[http://metronews.ca/news/halifax/590130/the-stanfields-rose-cousins-win-big-at-the-ecmas-in-halifax/ \"The Stanfields, Rose Cousins win big at the ECMAs in Halifax\"]. ''[[Metro International|Metro]]'', March 10, 2013.</ref> Described by some sources as \"the bastard children of [[AC/DC]] and [[Stan Rogers]]\",<ref name=independent /> the band blends a [[hard rock]] style with elements of traditional [[Atlantic Canada|Atlantic Canadian]] [[folk music]].<ref name=independent>[http://theindependent.ca/2013/03/14/double-ecma-winners-the-stanfields-embark-on-island-mini-tour/ \"Double ECMA winners The Stanfields embark on Island mini tour\"]. ''The Independent'', March 14, 2013.</ref>\n\n==Musical career==\nFormed in 2008, the band consists of [[vocals|lead vocalist]] and [[guitar]]ist Jon Landry, [[bass guitar|bassist]] Dillan Tate, [[guitar]]ist Jason MacIsaac, [[bouzouki]]/[[fiddle]] player Calen Kinney, and [[drum kit|drummer]] Mark Murphy.\nThe band formed and started out by playing [[Rock music|Rock]], [[Folk music|Folk]], and [[Country music|Country]] music cover songs during open mic performances at the Seahorse Tavern in Halifax, Nova Scotia.  They quickly gained local notoriety for their rowdy, entertaining live performances and were signed to Halifax independent label [[Groundswell Music]] in February 2010.\n\nThe Stanfields released their debut [[album]] ''Vanguard of the Young & Reckless'' in 2010, and followed up with ''Death & Taxes'' in 2012.<ref name=independent /> A third album, ''For King and Country'' was released on October 15, 2013.<ref name=annapolis>[http://www.annapoliscountyspectator.ca/Living/2013-12-05/article-3531321/Stanfields-to-rock-Evergreen-Theatre-December-7/1 \"The Stanfields to rock Evergreen Theatre\"].  ''Annapolis County Spectator'', December 5, 2013.</ref> The album contained 10 new songs written, performed and recorded completely acoustically.\n\nThe band's fourth full-length record, ''Modem Operandi'', was released on September 18, 2015.\n\nThe band is known for its powerful live show, and have toured mostly in [[Canada]] and [[Germany]].  In 2012 the band signed a [[distribution deal]] with [[Cologne]] based [[punk rock]] label, [[Rookie Records]].<ref name=\"rookie\">[http://www.rookierecords.de/en/category/bands/the-stanfields/ \"The Stanfields @ Rookie Records\"].  ''[[Rookie Records]]''</ref>\n\nIn early April 2020, in the context of the [[2019-20 coronavirus pandemic]], Nova Scotia premier [[Stephen McNeil]] made a speech in which he instructed Nova Scotians to \"stay the blazes home\" in order to protect the public from the spread of the virus. The Stanfields helped popularize the message by releasing a new song called Stay the Blazes Home. <ref name=\"blazes\">[https://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/nova-scotia/stay-the-blazes-home-inspires-music-merchandise-memes-1.5522068 \"Premier's 'Stay the blazes home' inspires music, merchandise, memes\"].  ''[[CBC News]]''</ref>\n\n== Awards ==\n[[2014 Music Nova Scotia Awards]] \u2013\nFolk Recording of the Year for ''For King and Country''\n\n[[2013 East Coast Music Awards]] \u2013\nGroup Recording of the Year for ''Death & Taxes'' and the Fan's Choice Entertainer of the Year.<ref name=metro />\n\n[[2013 Music Nova Scotia Awards]] \u2013\nGroup Recording of the Year for ''Death & Taxes'' and the Fan's Choice Entertainer of the Year.<ref name=cherald>[http://thechronicleherald.ca/artslife/1166672-classified-big-winner-at-music-nova-scotia-awards \"Classified big winner at Music Nova Scotia awards\"].  ''[[The Chronicle Herald]]'', November 11, 2013.</ref>\n\n== Discography ==\n''Vanguard of the Young & Reckless'' \u2013 GroundSwell Music (2010)\n\n''Death & Taxes'' \u2013 GroundSwell Music (2012)\n\n''For King and Country'' \u2013 GroundSwell Music (2013)\n\n''Modem Operandi'' \u2013 GroundSwell Music (2015)\n\n''Limboland'' \u2013 GroundSwell Music (2018)\n\n''Classic Fadeout'' \u2013 Groundswell Music (2020)\n\n==Band members==\n* Jon Landry \u2013 [[Guitar]], [[Vocals]]\n* Dillan Tate \u2013 [[Bass guitar|Bass Guitar]]\n* Calen Kinney \u2013 [[Bouzouki]], [[Fiddle]], [[Background Vocals]]\n* Jason MacIsaac \u2013 [[Guitar]], [[Background Vocals]]\n* Mark Murphy \u2013 [[Drums]]\n\n=== Former members ===\n* Craig Eugene Harris \u2013 [[Bass guitar|Bass Guitar]], [[Mandolin]], [[Background vocals|Background Vocals]] (2015)\n* Jason Wright \u2013 [[Bouzouki]],  [[Background Vocals]] (2015)\n* Charlie Coolen \u2013 [[Guitar]] (2008)\n* Jenny Wright \u2013 [[Vocals]] (2008)\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.thestanfields.ca/ Official website]\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Stanfields, The}}\n[[Category:Canadian rock music groups]]\n[[Category:Musical groups from Halifax, Nova Scotia]]\n[[Category:Musical groups established in 2008]]\n[[Category:2008 establishments in Nova Scotia]]\n", "text_old": "{{About|the Canadian [[folk rock]] band|the textile company|Stanfield%27s}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name = The Stanfields\n| background = group_or_band\n| image = The_Stanfields_-_Group_Photo.png\n| caption = From left to right: Dillan Tate, Jason MacIsaac, Jon Landry, Calen Kinney, and Mark Murphy\n| image_size =\n| genre = [[Folk rock]], [[punk rock]]\n| years_active        = {{Start date|2008}}\u2013present\n| origin = [[Halifax Regional Municipality|Halifax]], [[Nova Scotia]], Canada\n| label = Groundswell Music/[[Warner Music Canada]]. Rookie Records(EU)\n| associated_acts     =\n| website = http://www.thestanfields.ca\n| current_members = Jon Landry<br>Dillan Tate<br>Jason MacIsaac<br>Calen Kinney<br>Mark Murphy\n}}\n\n'''The Stanfields''' are a [[Canada|Canadian]] rock music group, based in [[Halifax Regional Municipality|Halifax]], [[Nova Scotia]].<ref name=metro>[http://metronews.ca/news/halifax/590130/the-stanfields-rose-cousins-win-big-at-the-ecmas-in-halifax/ \"The Stanfields, Rose Cousins win big at the ECMAs in Halifax\"]. ''[[Metro International|Metro]]'', March 10, 2013.</ref> Described by some sources as \"the bastard children of [[AC/DC]] and [[Stan Rogers]]\",<ref name=independent /> the band blends a [[hard rock]] style with elements of traditional [[Atlantic Canada|Atlantic Canadian]] [[folk music]].<ref name=independent>[http://theindependent.ca/2013/03/14/double-ecma-winners-the-stanfields-embark-on-island-mini-tour/ \"Double ECMA winners The Stanfields embark on Island mini tour\"]. ''The Independent'', March 14, 2013.</ref>\n\n==Musical career==\nFormed in 2008, the band consists of [[vocals|lead vocalist]] and [[guitar]]ist Jon Landry, [[bass guitar|bassist]] Dillan Tate, [[guitar]]ist Jason MacIsaac, [[bouzouki]]/[[fiddle]] player Calen Kinney, and [[drum kit|drummer]] Mark Murphy.\nThe band formed and started out by playing [[Rock music|Rock]], [[Folk music|Folk]], and [[Country music|Country]] music cover songs during open mic performances at the Seahorse Tavern in Halifax, Nova Scotia.  They quickly gained local notoriety for their rowdy, entertaining live performances and were signed to Halifax independent label [[Groundswell Music]] in February 2010.\n\nThe Stanfields released their debut [[album]] ''[[Vanguard of the Young & Reckless]]'' in 2010, and followed up with ''[[Death & Taxes (The Stanfields album)|Death & Taxes]]'' in 2012.<ref name=independent /> A third album, ''[[For King and Country (The Stanfields album)|For King and Country]]'' was released on October 15, 2013.<ref name=annapolis>[http://www.annapoliscountyspectator.ca/Living/2013-12-05/article-3531321/Stanfields-to-rock-Evergreen-Theatre-December-7/1 \"The Stanfields to rock Evergreen Theatre\"].  ''Annapolis County Spectator'', December 5, 2013.</ref> The album contained 10 new songs written, performed and recorded completely acoustically.\n\nThe band's fourth full-length record, ''[[Modem Operandi,|Modem Operandi]]'', was released on September 18, 2015.\n\nThe band is known for its powerful live show, and have toured mostly in [[Canada]] and [[Germany]].  In 2012 the band signed a [[distribution deal]] with [[Cologne]] based [[punk rock]] label, [[Rookie Records]].<ref name=\"rookie\">[http://www.rookierecords.de/en/category/bands/the-stanfields/ \"The Stanfields @ Rookie Records\"].  ''[[Rookie Records]]''</ref>\n\nIn early April 2020, in the context of the [[2019-20 coronavirus pandemic]], Nova Scotia premier [[Stephen McNeil]] made a speech in which he instructed Nova Scotians to \"stay the blazes home\" in order to protect the public from the spread of the virus. The Stanfields helped popularize the message by releasing a new song called Stay the Blazes Home. <ref name=\"blazes\">[https://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/nova-scotia/stay-the-blazes-home-inspires-music-merchandise-memes-1.5522068 \"Premier's 'Stay the blazes home' inspires music, merchandise, memes\"].  ''[[CBC News]]''</ref>\n\n== Awards ==\n[[2014 Music Nova Scotia Awards]]\nFolk Recording of the Year for ''For King and Country''\n\n[[2013 East Coast Music Awards]]-\nGroup Recording of the Year for ''Death & Taxes'' and the Fan's Choice Entertainer of the Year.<ref name=metro />\n\n[[2013 Music Nova Scotia Awards]]-\nGroup Recording of the Year for ''Death & Taxes'' and the Fan's Choice Entertainer of the Year.<ref name=cherald>[http://thechronicleherald.ca/artslife/1166672-classified-big-winner-at-music-nova-scotia-awards \"Classified big winner at Music Nova Scotia awards\"].  ''[[The Chronicle Herald]]'', November 11, 2013.</ref>\n\n== Discography ==\n''Vanguard of the Young & Reckless'' - GroundSwell Music (2010)\n\n''Death & Taxes'' - GroundSwell Music (2012)\n\n''For King and Country'' - GroundSwell Music (2013)\n\n''Modem Operandi'' - GroundSwell Music (2015)\n\n''Limboland'' - GroundSwell Music (2018)\n\n''Classic Fadeout'' - Groundswell Music (2020)\n\n==Band members==\n* Jon Landry \u2013 [[Guitar]], [[Vocals]]\n* Dillan Tate - [[Bass guitar|Bass Guitar]]\n* Calen Kinney \u2013 [[Bouzouki]], [[Fiddle]], [[Background Vocals]]\n* Jason MacIsaac \u2013 [[Guitar]], [[Background Vocals]]\n* Mark Murphy \u2013 [[Drums]]\n\n=== Former members ===\n* Craig Eugene Harris - [[Bass guitar|Bass Guitar]], [[Mandolin]], [[Background vocals|Background Vocals]] (2015)\n* Jason Wright \u2013 [[Bouzouki]],  [[Background Vocals]] (2015)\n* Charlie Coolen \u2013 [[Guitar]] (2008)\n* Jenny Wright \u2013 [[Vocals]] (2008)\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.thestanfields.ca/ Official website]\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Stanfields, The}}\n[[Category:Canadian rock music groups]]\n[[Category:Musical groups from Halifax, Nova Scotia]]\n[[Category:Musical groups established in 2008]]\n[[Category:2008 establishments in Nova Scotia]]\n", "name_user": "PKT", "label": "safe", "comment": "unlinked album names and other copyedits", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Stanfields"}
{"title_page": "Anton Polyutkin", "text_new": "{{Eastern Slavic name|Sergeyevich|Polyutkin}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Anton Polyutkin\n| image = \n| full_name = Anton Sergeyevich Polyutkin\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1993|02|2|df=yes}}\n| birth_place = [[Naberezhnye Chelny]], [[Russia]]\n| height = {{height|m=1.91}}\n| position = [[Defender (association football)|Centre back]]\n| currentclub = [[FC Tyumen]]\n| clubnumber = 20\n| years1 = 2011\u20132014 | clubs1 = [[PFC CSKA Moscow]]                 | caps1 =  0 | goals1 = 0\n| years2 = 2013\u20132014 | clubs2 = \u2192 [[FC Yenisey Krasnoyarsk]] (loan) | caps2 =  1 | goals2 = 0\n| years3 = 2014\u20132016 | clubs3 = [[FC Solyaris Moscow]]              | caps3 = 50 | goals3 = 1\n| years4 = 2016      | clubs4 = [[FC Montana]]                      | caps4 =  7 | goals4 = 0\n| years5 = 2017      | clubs5 = [[FC Academia Chi\u0219in\u0103u]]            | caps5 =  9 | goals5 = 1\n| years6 = 2017\u20132019 | clubs6 = [[FC Sibir Novosibirsk]]            | caps6 = 47 | goals6 = 1\n| years7 = 2019\u2013     | clubs7 = [[FC Tyumen]]                       | caps7 = 16 | goals7 = 2\n| nationalyears1 = 2009 | nationalteam1 = [[Russia national under-16 football team|Russia U-16]] | nationalcaps1 = 6 | nationalgoals1 = 0\n| nationalyears2 = 2010 | nationalteam2 = [[Russia national under-17 football team|Russia U-17]] | nationalcaps2 = 3 | nationalgoals2 = 0\n| pcupdate = 00:00, 15 November 2019 (UTC)\n| ntupdate = \n}}\n\n'''Anton Sergeyevich Polyutkin''' ({{lang-ru|\u0410\u043d\u0442\u043e\u043d \u0421\u0435\u0440\u0433\u0435\u0435\u0432\u0438\u0447 \u041f\u043e\u043b\u044e\u0442\u043a\u0438\u043d}}; born 2 February 1993) is a [[Russia]]n [[association football|football]] [[Defender (association football)|defender]]. He plays for [[FC Tyumen]].\n\n==Career==\nPolyutkin made his debut in the [[Russian Football National League]] for [[FC Yenisey Krasnoyarsk]] on 27 October 2013 in a game against [[FC Arsenal Tula]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[Russian Football Union]] |url=http://rfspro.ru/cgi-bin/player/script2.cgi?par1=117878 |title=Career Summary |date=28 January 2014 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140201192002/http://rfspro.ru/cgi-bin/player/script2.cgi?par1=117878 |archivedate=1 February 2014 }}</ref> In March 2017, he joined [[Moldova]]n club [[FC Academia Chi\u0219in\u0103u|Academia Chi\u0219in\u0103u]]; he made his debut against [[FC Saxan|Saxan]] on 17 March.<ref>{{cite web | title = \u041c\u043e\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0432\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439 \"\u0434\u0437\u044e\u0434\u043e\u0438\u0441\u0442\" \u0434\u0435\u0431\u044e\u0442\u0438\u0440\u043e\u0432\u0430\u043b \u0437\u0430 \"\u0410\u043a\u0430\u0434\u0435\u043c\u0438\u044e\" | url = http://moldova.sports.md/football/national_division/news/17-03-2017/135971/moskovskij_dz_udoist_deb_utiroval_za_akademiju/ | publisher = moldova.sports.md | date = 17 March 2017 | language = Russian}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Sportbox.ru|Futbol/Anton-Sergeevich-Polyutkin-Futbol-02021993}}\n* {{Soccerway|anton-polyutkin/263400}}\n\n{{FC Tyumen squad}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Polyutkin, Anton}}\n[[Category:1993 births]]\n[[Category:People from Naberezhnye Chelny]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Russian footballers]]\n[[Category:Russia youth international footballers]]\n[[Category:FC Yenisey Krasnoyarsk players]]\n[[Category:FC Solyaris Moscow players]]\n[[Category:PFC Montana players]]\n[[Category:FC Academia Chi\u0219in\u0103u players]]\n[[Category:First Professional Football League (Bulgaria) players]]\n[[Category:Moldovan National Division players]]\n[[Category:Russian expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Bulgaria]]\n[[Category:Russian expatriate sportspeople in Bulgaria]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Moldova]]\n[[Category:Russian expatriate sportspeople in Moldova]]\n[[Category:Association football defenders]]\n[[Category:FC Sibir